 
1) ensure that you have python3 active

python -V

2) get location of python 3 to prevent virtualenv creating env with python2

which python
 
3) with that location create virtual env

virtualenv -p /usr/bin/python3 env 
. env/bin/activate

4) install packages

pip install -r requirements.txt

5) 

python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate

6)

pytest -v
or
python manage.py test

7)

python manage.py runserver

8)

visit url at http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/

take a look at curl requests
